From: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Sat, 12 Jun 2021 22:00:05 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] igc: Fix an error handling path in 'igc_probe()'
References: bsn#19
Patch-mainline: v5.10.54

[ Upstream commit c6bc9e5ce5d37cb3e6b552f41b92a193db1806ab ]

If an error occurs after a 'pci_enable_pcie_error_reporting()' call, it
must be undone by a corresponding 'pci_disable_pcie_error_reporting()'
call, as already done in the remove function.

Fixes: c9a11c23ceb6 ("igc: Add netdev")
Signed-off-by: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Tested-by: Dvora Fuxbrumer <dvorax.fuxbrumer@linux.intel.com>
Acked-by: Sasha Neftin <sasha.neftin@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tony Nguyen <anthony.l.nguyen@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Kai Liu <kai.liu@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_main.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_main.c
index 4b58dd97a7c0..b9fe2785f573 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igc/igc_main.c
@@ -5223,6 +5223,7 @@ static int igc_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev,
 err_ioremap:
 	free_netdev(netdev);
 err_alloc_etherdev:
+	pci_disable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
 	pci_release_mem_regions(pdev);
 err_pci_reg:
 err_dma:
